snippet.textDisplay:
"A slow pandemic will not be remembered by the history books"
That aged poorly.  Covid may have ended up being slow, 2+ years, but it is definitely getting remembered by the history books.  It had many huge, and in some cases permanent, effects on our society.  It caused fundamental changes to work, education, worship, medicine, and politics, and shortages of food and supplies that will ripple out for years to come.
